INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (894, 888, 312, 5, 'A very good overview of undergraduate probability. This is not going to be a very rigorous book that will give you as much detail as other more specialized textbooks will, but that''s not why you should be considering this book. This book is full of carefully chosen examples, along with the main ideas, explanations, intuitions that are required. The book still does explain all definitions clearly (with proof often) and approaches ideas from a set-theoretic perspective -- which is important if you are considering any further study of probability.In conclusion, this is a great support material to be used for reference or as a refresher, NOT a main textbook (although you would definitely still get a lot out of it //edit: after giving it some thought, it COULD be used as a main text to learn from given how much stuff is packed in, although I would still very much classify it as a great supporting text). A lot of care was put into the book, it is well structured, well paced, and very approachable.Pishro-Nik has the book online for free (generously), so check it out yourself before buying and see if you agree.');
