INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1002, 967, 363, 5, 'A prequel to his novel, NOS4A2, Joe Hill has created another fantastic book worthy of any fan of horror or the comic book genre. What is cool about this story is how we, the readers, get to learn more of Charlie Manx''s past. Hill is able to build further into this world he has created with all his other books and that is just awesome in my opinion. A person could read this book by its self and enjoy it I think, but l think you should read NOS 4A2 as well.The book itself is a very nice glossed hardcover, with nice glossed pages as well. Mr. Hill and Mr. Wilson were very compatible with one another and helped build upon Hill''s previous work. I liked C.P. Wilson III artwork a lot but I will admit I will always be curious what it would have looked like if Gabriel Rodriguez had handled the artwork (he worked with Hill on the Locke and Key series).Overall...great story, great art, great book, great buy');
