INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1239, 1144, 445, 3, 'The first book in the trilogy was great, the second was good, but this one was merely average. That said, I greatly enjoyed the trilogy and would certainly recommend it.The primary reason I can give this only three stars is because I found the characters'' dialogue lacking. Often it seemed that characters would use idioms and tones of speech which were forced and out-of-place. Also, the absurdity of the Presger translators struck me as a unnecessary attempt to add levity to the book, however their interactions were a bit too contrived.Overall I enjoyed the plot of the final book and felt the ending was satisfactory although a bit rushed. Indeed I will seek out more of Leckie''s novels based just on the brilliance of the first Radch book.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1240, 1145, 445, 5, 'A bit slow moving at first, the book picks up its pace as it moves along. Great world building and unforgettable characters. For me the second two books lacked the mystery and edge that the first had, but nonetheless super entertaining. And wrapped up but with nuggets for future stories, i hope.');
