INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1257, 1156, 451, 5, 'This is the 2nd book in the trilogy and Pierce Brown continues with unpredictable plots and great turns and twists.Honestly guys! one of the BEST and unpredictable trilogies i''ve ever read... and I''ve read the LOT of them! I am a big fan of fantasy and epic novels. read a few books per month and prefer Series or Trilogies. I have been impressed by some over the years (e.g. Lightbringer, Night Angel) but this trilogy by Pierce Brown has blown me away. Kept me on the edge of my seat. Just unbelievably good with twist after twist. You NEVER see those twists coming!I also liked the development of his characters and the fact that some of them die along the way, when you least expect it!');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1258, 1157, 451, 5, 'Where do I even begin? After thoroughly enjoying Red Rising, I had high expectations for book 2. It''s a very different feel from book 1, but it has all of the same things I loved about the first installment. And THAT ENDING THOUGH. To say I''m shook would be a gross understatement. Quite simply one of the most shocking moments I''ve ever experienced in books, TV, or movies. Absolutely incredible. Cannot wait to get into book 3.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1259, 1158, 451, 3, 'Starting to think this series is overrated. How many stupid decisions can the protagonist make to keep the plot moving forward? How many times do we have to go through another variation of the setback before the story goes somewhere. So far very repetitive basically same thing happens repeatedly 1 step forward 2 steps back. The logical flaws are frustrating. Example without spoilers if you kinda someone for a hostage you can do more than just kill them once..ie torture repeatedly. The author acts as though holding a hostage gives you no leverage to push the plot is a desired direction...and that is another setback. Let''s move this forward in book 3 shall we?! Yes I''ll read it. The universe is interesting and hopefully the story catches up soon!');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1260, 1159, 451, 5, 'If your someone who reads a book for its action and it''s linear story, I would not recommend this book. This book and the first one have a lot of amazing description, AND THE BEST character development I have ever came across. Heavy readers will dig this series, as you will witness Darrow race to liberate society from the Golds in his carved body. So mind boggling and superior, YOU just really have to read it to know what I mean.I read the last 100 pages in one sitting, and has a hell of a twister in the end. I can''t wait for the Morning Star!Good Job Dan, I will for sure be reading many more of your literature.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1261, 1160, 451, 5, 'Really great story, can''t wait to continue !  This book is awesome, action, romance and suspense. When you think everything is fine BANG! everything is upside down in second.Highly recommended!!!!!!!');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1262, 1161, 451, 5, 'WOW!! This series is fantastic and we were so keen to get the whole series after reading the first book that Amazon was the only way to order so we could get to reading as quickly as possible!');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1263, 1063, 451, 5, 'Loved both Book 1 & 2. Wasn''t sure what to expect from the author, but was impressed. I found the series included compelling characters & a plot that continued to evolve while always leaving me surprised at the turn of events. Have pre ordered Book 3.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1264, 1162, 451, 5, 'This is the second book of an amazing series, it''s like game of thrones meets hunger games in space! It''s a great read that continues an awesome storyline around a very relatable protagonist.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1411, 1052, 474, 5, 'Beautifully written. Captivating. Thrilling. Suspenseful. Michael is an amazing author. I wouldn''t hesitate in reading this time and time again');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1265, 1163, 468, 5, 'I loved the movie, and I was worried that the book would ruin a great cinematic experience.  If nothing else, the book is a fantastic companion which helps flesh out characters which were previously left a little thin.  There''s a much clearer depiction of motivations and events which even a 3 hour movie could not flesh out.All in all one of the most satisfying reads in recent years.');
