INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1382, 1223, 470, 5, 'I won''t get into the story but if you liked the first two, the author does not disappoint in this one. Intriguing how the author uses history and myths to bring alive action figures. In this book we find that the villains are having a harder time dealing with their failures to capture the twins and the last pages of the codex. We don''t seem to be finding any "good elders" that don''t have one issue or another. But still things are moving ahead. The author does an excellent job of moving from one battle to another without repetition of tactics. That''s nice. You don''t know what will be the outcome. The author has hinted that eventually Josh will be captured by the dark side. Yet Josh seems to pull the team out of trouble over and over again. What can I say about the cliff hanger at the end of the book!! Woww. Jumped into the next one already.');
