INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1488, 1309, 488, 5, 'What can I say. It’s Jack Reacher and like all the others it’s great. If you’ve never read a Jack Reacher story then I strongly suggest you start now. Over twenty books by author Lee Child featuring this fictional character, an ex military police officer now casually roaming across the U.S. running into trouble wherever he goes.  This series is an amazing read. Not necessary to read them in order but if you want to then you should start with ‘No Middle Name’ as it has two short stories that feature Jack in his teens');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1489, 1331, 488, 5, 'Excellent plot with protagonist Jack Reacher, an US ex-army Military Policeman. The MP''s are a hated group among other army types because they are the ones who police all the other army soldiers no matter what rank they are. Reacher has left the army and now uses his investigative and other learned talents to help people in whichever state he finds himself in. The stories are all good mystery-thrillers and unique in their plots. Reacher is always the good guy, who helps ordinary citizens and local police to solve a problem. I have read these books in order and think it helps to do that as you get to follow Reacher''s path after his army days are over. A few of the books have a plot that takes you back to his army days to give you a full picture of who Jack Reacher is.');
