INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1798, 1512, 652, 3, 'I have bought the audio book (a first experience). I did not notice that I ordered the MP3-CD. So I could not play it on my audio system and my computer (although recent) could not read it either. I had to buy the audio book from iTunes which, to my surprise, was cheaper (and I was unable to transfer it on my iPhone). The description of the audio book advertises a number of voices. I thought that the voices would speak different characters in the narration of the book, but no; each voice speaks all the characters for a portion of the book. I did not enjoy the first two voices which were too rough for my taste. I would have liked the main character to be more developed, to know him more personally like I came to know, love and admire Ender and Bean in other of O.S.C.''s books.Pathfinder');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1799, 1513, 652, 5, 'Card''s created a really intriguing world to play in. The blend of fantasy elements with a little sci-fi mixed in was really extraordinary and played with my head quite a bit. As always, he''s got great ideas tossed into the dialogue that pause and make me think. It''s an incredible novel, and I can''t wait to get into the next one when it comes out.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1800, 1514, 362, 5, '"I have never told this story nor shall mortal man see this manuscript until I have passed over for eternity.  I know that the average human mind will not believe what it can not grasp......"Written in 1912 this book is well written for its time and has intrigued countless generations of readers.  I get the feeling that this story is being told over a campfire.Captain Carter is telling the story form memory as an old man of his adventures here on earth and on the planet of Barsoom (Mars).  There are encounters with many strain creatures, situations, and yes even a "Princess of Mars."This is a part is a series by the writer that brought us "Tarzan."  The intro to the book alone will capture your imagination.The Great Book of Tarzan');
