INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1993, 1568, 736, 5, 'Excellent trilogy. The show maintains some of the elements of the books but the books add huge amounts of superb detail. A little graphic and disturbing in places but still a fantastic read. Really enjoyed the outlandish usage of the English language it is extremely rare I need to look up a word but I had to do it repeatedly. The codex by the same Author is alright but not as good.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1994, 1569, 736, 4, 'I started reading this trilogy in anticipation of the TV show. While I really didn''t end up liking the show at all, the books are fantastic. I feel like all three books get off to a slow start but it makes up for it in later chapters.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1995, 1570, 736, 5, 'This book was amazing. It starts out fairly light, then descends into many very dark places. I did not expect this and it only made me love this trilogy more. I''m not going to give you a play-by-play. You can get that yourself by reading this gripping tale. I read it in a mere few hours as I just could not put this book down.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (1996, 1571, 736, 4, 'This trilogy dips a doe into a world of magic but is written with adults in mind unlike the Harry Potter / Lord of the Rings genre. The storytelling is good but the writing is exceptional! It was the perfect summer cottage fiction as an antidote to everyday seriousness. If you could use a bit of magic in your life I recommend it!');
