INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2017, 1582, 745, 5, 'A new author to me but I was not disappointed. Having been a fan of Lee Child for years I didn''t know what to expect but Ms. Capri kept me intrigued from the first page.  I will certainly be following more on Jack Reacher by this author and look forward to other books she has written.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2018, 1583, 745, 1, 'Interesting concept.  About a third of the way through, I started to re-read The Killing Floor, and it was just as enjoyable as the first time I read it.  But when I came back to continue reading Capri''s book, I realized I just did not like it at all.  I started skipping ahead, but it still could not hold my interest.  I could not finish it.  Will not be reading any more of this series.  Would rather re-read the real Reacher books.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2019, 1584, 745, 5, 'I was happy to read Lee Child''s endorsement of this alternate FBI thriller. I was intrigued that a "nebulous" Jack Reacher could create a connector for a totally different and equally enjoyable read.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2020, 1585, 745, 1, 'Very poor plot.  Reliance on hidden mechanisms that are never explained.  Fails to divulge the reasons behind the several murders committed.  Fails to explain or justify quite patently absurd behaviour by supposed FBI agents.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2021, 1586, 745, 5, 'Can''t ever get enough of Reacher and even though these are back story concepts they fit in well with the legend.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2022, 1587, 745, 3, 'Had trouble following who''s who and the plot lines.  Have to really pay attention or take notes to keep things straight.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2023, 1588, 745, 2, 'Interesting premise, but poorly executed.  Flash over substance and numerous inconsistencies in the little details.  Required many leaps of faith.  Not at all up to the quality of the Reacher books by Lee Childs.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2024, 1589, 745, 4, 'Nicely done ,,a very different angle referencing another authors main character');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2025, 1590, 486, 5, 'It may be called book 16 in the series but Child has paid proper respects to both his creation and to himself by doing a long-awaited prequel as to Reacher''s origins. It is as good as any other book in the series, perhaps better considering the timline. This review written in 2017 and it should be noted that the number of people who still read books declines every day, as does the number of writers who still make a living writing bestselling novels. Therefore, an extraordinary work on many levels, and one that should be enjoyed, maybe even cherished.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2026, 1591, 486, 5, 'After a couple of less than exceptional efforts it appears Lee Child had his act together for this one. Written in the first person, a format I prefer for the Reacher novels, it downplays the violence and concentrates more on Reacher''s analytical skills. It was a very enjoyable read. I read it beginning to end in one session. Hopefully he will write more about the military adventures of Reacher.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2027, 1592, 486, 5, 'Picked out this read by fluke... Turned out to be one of best reads i have had in a while!  A Lee Child fan I now am.Couldn''t but it down. Well done!');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2028, 1593, 486, 5, 'EVERYTHING BY THIS AUTHOR IS FANTASTIC, EVEN THE ONES THAT ARE NOT JACK REACHER BOOKSYOU WILL NOT REGRET YOU PURCHASES');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2029, 1336, 486, 5, 'I ordered three "Jack Reacher" novels together.What can I say......they''re always a great read, and they were shipped at warp speed.  I got them the next day, I think.  I couldn''t plan a better order/delivery.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2030, 1594, 486, 5, 'Another Jack Reacher book.  This is one of the most intriging characters I have ever read.  You never know what to expect from these books and I find I can''t put it down once I start reading it.  I just have to find out how everything works out.  I recommend this book to any Jack Reacher fans.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2031, 1595, 486, 4, 'Good Lee Child novel, not his best but still a good story, well worth the read.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2033, 1597, 750, 4, 'Lee Child is consistently good in this series.  Master of a different, effective writing style, he never fails to entertain.The only criticism I offer is that the detailed description of the fight scenes seem too focused; giving me the impression that this focus is critical to the plot; when actually, I don''t believe it is.  Hope the next volumes are less formulaic - drifts into town, meets girl, uncovers sinister plot, defeats bad guys while getting clobbered, has sex with girl(s), loses girl, gains toothbrush, leaves town.  There are exceptions, but this is a general thread of the post-military volumes.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2034, 1598, 750, 5, 'Great story as always, keeps you guessing and wondering the whole time! Well written, so well, you want the story to keep on going and find out what mystery and case he’ll solve next! Lee Child’s ability to write and come up with these story lines makes it all believable and worthwhile to read!');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2035, 1599, 750, 5, 'This is an excellent story, well told, and should not disappoint any Lee Child fan.  All the Reacher books are great but this is one of the best.  It starts out with a text book murder enquiry, gathering overwhelming evidence leading to an arrest which it seems must be of the right man. Even Reacher, though specifically asked for by the accused, believes he is guilty and he wants him convicted.  But all is not as it seems and it takes Reacher and his many talents to unravel the twisted tale and deliver his own inimitable version of justice.Jim French');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2036, 1342, 750, 5, 'Child’s always delivers with Reacher.  Just wish the ending of the novel would introduce the next, rather than having to work out the order of each book in the series.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2037, 1329, 750, 5, 'I''ve read all of his novels & anxiously awaiting his next one The whole Jack Reacher series is great, I''d recommend them all. The only problem is the movie. Jack Reacher is 6'' 5" 230 lbs. Tom Cruise is 5'' & maybe 150 lbs, Jack Reacher should be Dwayne Johnson instead,');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2038, 508, 750, 5, 'Another great book by an exceptional author. What a mind, to continually keep a spell binding plot in motion right to the end.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2039, 1333, 750, 4, 'One shot is an interesting story. Lots of twists and turns. I figured out some of them but like most Reacher books there’s always something you’re not expecting. I enjoyed this one and didn’t want to put it down.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2040, 1600, 750, 5, 'I personally  could do without the detailed intimacy. Scenes! The power of the fast moving plot did not need that.  Otherwise it was well written and  kept a reader involved and eager for the next discovery !  I would not hesitate to recommend this book to those I know. Like to read these type of mysteries,  I gave the rating I did because it held my attention right to the end.  I found it very hard to put down, and eager to get back to it when I did.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2041, 1055, 741, 4, 'Of course his being there just as the abduction happens is a bit too much, but other than that a good read. Not unlike the coincidence of the first book.But without those, not much of a story. Well written and a good fast paced novel.I quite enjoyed it. A friend recommended the series (avoided them due to the terrible movies), on to the 3rd.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2042, 1353, 741, 5, 'I am obviouslly late to the Jack Reacher universe. I saw the movie and loved it but Tom Cruise is not 6 ft 5 in  as the character in the book is....but he still did a great job as Jack Reacher. This  led me to the books, I always find books so much better than movies, and this book was no exception. Right from beginning to end it kept me captivated (ironic if you read the book).Well written......great story.....just beleivable enough to make it interesting! LOL  I will be reading Book 3. 5 of 5 stars');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2043, 1601, 741, 5, 'A thoroughly engaging read,  a "page-turning"; not because multiple stories end each chapter as a cliffhanger to be picked up two chapters later,  but because the stories move and the character is real and complex.  My wife and I enjoy reviewing the storyline after both completing a book in the series,  to try and find flaws in the storyline.  Generally,  we don''t.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2044, 1602, 741, 5, 'As to the details... these are all great if you like Jack. The only thing I chuckle about is how we know Jack is a big lumbering hulk of a man, yet the movie casts tiny t. cruise as “jack” in the movie version. Don’t get me wrong, I’m a Cruise fan, but he is miscast because of his size only.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2045, 1603, 741, 5, 'Like all the Lee Child novels this one has a tight plot woven through with engaging characters and lots of action. Jack Reacher is a version of the hero we all wanted to be as kids, who gets the girl and sees that the bad guys get what they deserve with an ethos right out of the old West.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2046, 1343, 741, 5, 'First reacher book I''ve read and really enjoyed the characters and plot.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2047, 1329, 741, 5, 'I''ve read all of his novels & anxiously awaiting his next one The whole Jack Reacher series is great, I''d recommend them all. The only problem is the movie. Jack Reacher is 6'' 5" 230 lbs. Tom Cruise is 5'' & maybe 150 lbs, Jack Reacher should be Dwayne Johnson instead,');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2048, 492, 741, 5, 'Reacher is an excellent read, concise, crisp, great action, with well developed characters and a hero who does what''s right without any angst. An embodiment of chivalry with all the crap stripped away a righteous hero who gives the bad guys what they deserve without any hesitation. Lee Child gave me a real hero in fiction. Reminds me of the kind of men and women we call the greatest generation.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2049, 1604, 759, 4, 'By reading the information on the copyright page, the reader will note that the stories in this book have been culled from over a half dozen publications, possibly many more.  As such, it seems reasonable to assume that they were written over a span of a great number of years.  I would have found it helpful had the original copyright dates of each entry been included so one could, in some ways, track Bradbury''s development as a writer.Having said that, I did enjoy this book for the very variety that seems to have put off some of the reviewers here.  There are stories that are pure Sci-Fi, others that are perfect examples of the horror genre, some that make us want to laugh and/or cry, and many that combine several of these aspects.One of the latter that I found particularly moving is "Lafayette, Farewell."  In it, an elderly man who knows that he is to die soon begins to relive the air battles he fought as a fighter pilot over France during World War I.  Every night, he sees and hears the planes of those brave young men who died as he successfully shot their planes out of the sky.  He now feels guilty over taking the lives of those innocent young pilots who, like himself, were sent into a war not of their own making.He fears that he will be consigned to hell for what he has done, and he asks his neighbor how he can, at this late date, be forgiven.  His neighbor suggests that, since they, in their planes, are appearing over his house nightly before parachuting to their deaths in his back yard, he plainly and simply, ask them for their forgiveness.  In a very moving scene, he does just that and they indicate that he is forgiven.This is really a touching story, one of my favorites in the book.  There are others equally rewarding to read along with some that are among Bradbury''s lesser works.  I for one, am glad to see as many of Bradbury''s stories as possible anthologized in books such as _THE TOYNBEE CONVECTOR_.  I''m afraid that those that aren''t, and which appeared in more obscure, older Sci-Fi magazines, may be lost to us forever.  In my opinion, all of his writing is worth preserving for readers of the future.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2098, 1625, 773, 3, 'Only read a bit, so no opinion. But since I read the first eight, it should continue to be enjoyable.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2099, 1633, 773, 4, 'Omega Force is at it again. Those guys should fine some safer forms of entertainment, but until they do, I"ll keep reading.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2100, 1634, 773, 5, 'Loved the book, great continuation of the series.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2050, 1605, 759, 4, 'I was disappointed when I read One More For the Road.  That was not on of Mr. Bradbury''s better collections.  But The Toynbee Convector is full of all the tales and ideas we know Mr. Bradbury is capable of.We begin with the title story involving time travel.  Next we get a dark tale of mysterious trapdoor.  From there we meet ghosts, banshees and things that are not there.  We return to Green Town, see romances, experience jealousies. and meet writers.The stories cover a very broad spectrum of Mr. Bradbury''s work.  Because of that, some who read the collection straight through (as I did) might feel bounced around a little by the changing themes.  Others, like myself, will savor each story for what it is, from literary popcorn to written gem.If you like the author''s older collections, then this is one for you.  If you thought One More For The Road was his best, there will still be something in her for you.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2051, 1606, 759, 5, 'Bradbury continues to shine with this book. It is a shame that it is out-of-print. If you find it somewhere, snag it. Or, snag three or four copies and share them with your friends!');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2052, 1158, 759, 5, 'The Book "The Toynbee Convector" by Ray Bradbury is a very good title. This might be his best collection of short stories ever. Every story is unique in its own way, each having a different ending. Like Bradbury''s  most famous piece, "Fahrenheit 451",  most stories take place in  the future. This is a great read for any type of reader.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2053, 1158, 759, 5, 'The Book "The Toynbee Convector" by Ray Bradbury is a very good title. This might be his best collection of short stories ever. Every story is unique in its own way, each having a different ending. Like Bradbury''s  most famous piece, "Fahrenheit 451",  most stories take place in  the future. This is a great read for any type of reader.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2054, 1607, 759, 5, 'that Ray Bradbury has ever written, in my humble opinion, is ''Lafayette, Farewell''. Buy it if only for this one story. The rest of the book is decent, definitely worth reading, though not quite as good as much of his earlier works. I would hate to think that his writing is still as good, but my own sense of wonder has dried up a bit...');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2055, 1608, 759, 5, 'Ray Bradbury''s tales in this book are both inspiring and entertaining.  My favorite aspect of these stories is that in many of them, Bradbury seems to take a common event and throw a slight twist of science fiction into story.  Each story paints a picture that part of me takes to heart everytime I  read it.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2056, 1609, 759, 5, 'This book the ''Toynbee Convector'' is a very clever collection of Bradbury''s works.  Each story is unique and it is well worth searching used book stores for this one.  I enjoyed this one tremendously as it continues  in the tradition of ''The Martian Chronicles'' and ''The Illustrated Man'' with  it''s creativity.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2057, 1507, 768, 5, 'I enjoyed this book for the mystery surrounding the phage and for the portrayal of an hero that is still human.I would''ve enjoyed the book to be longer.This trilogy is my first from this author and I will certainly look up his other books');
