INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2161, 1669, 792, 5, 'BV Larson has done it again. Another amazing read from the Undying Mercenary universe. Can’t wait for it to come out on audiobook and listen to it on the long boring drives.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2162, 492, 792, 5, 'Book 10. Love it. McGill is back again with his old ways in hand. Keep the books coming please Mr Larson!');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2163, 1670, 792, 5, 'Another great undying merc story. Waiting for the next one.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2164, 1626, 785, 4, 'I enjoyed the book very much and would like to see a follow on with McGill.  The idea of soldiers being reanimated after death to fight again is an intriguing premise for new stories opening up many potential options for new campaigns, relationships, strategies etc. (and storylines.)  I am an avid fan of BV Larson and have read most of his stories.  I eagerly await the next in the Star Force series as well as a follow up to the eternal soldier- McGill.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2165, 1671, 785, 5, 'I like books where the protagonist starts out as a bit of a loser and then grows into his/her capabilities and talents. If you like this too, along with reptilian enemies and sci-fi battle tech, this book is for you. In particular, I enjoyed the exploration of the change to the dynamic of combat when the participants can ( mostly) count on being reanimated after death.  I would very much like this book to be the first in a series.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2166, 1672, 785, 5, 'This is an older series and I really enjoyed his writing in this opener. The dialog is reasonably clever and the combination of fun and desperation is pretty appealing in what amounts to space opera. If you like Star Force or another series by him, check this one out for sure.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2167, 1673, 785, 5, 'I mostly read fantasy novels, but i''ve been hitting alot of scifi novels lately, steel world is one of the best i have read. Larson has come up with some new brilliant realistic concepts that I have yet to read about. his characters are well thought out, not brilliant but for only one book so far in the series they are pretty good, he has a great sense of humour in this novel. I highly recommend it');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2168, 1674, 785, 5, 'I bought it for the presentation value as I listen on Audible.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2169, 653, 785, 5, 'This is another exciting, action-packed story from B. V. Larson. It is fast-paced, with great alien tech and monsters and all the gore anyone could want. Reminds me a bit if the movie: " Starship Troopers".');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2170, 1675, 785, 5, 'Best story I have read in several weeks.  Interesting premise and good development of characters including an excellent variety.  Unpredictable plot and excellent action sequences.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2171, 517, 785, 5, 'I''ve read several other books by this author and to be honest at first I was a bit anoyed that this wasn''t a new book in a seires he has on going but now I think I''ll be more upset if one of his next books is not a continuation of  this new world he has created and of McGrill. I hope to see more soon!');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2172, 653, 786, 5, 'This eighth novel of the “Undying Mercenaries “ series starts to get more political, as our hero rises in rank and starts to become involved in the plots and intrigues of the highest levels of the earth’s government. Still lots of fighting and dying.');
