INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2246, 1416, 796, 1, 'Where to even start. About 20 pages in you''ll realize it''s going to be littered with errors. Thought I was losing my mind at one point because I thought I was rereading things I had already read; that''s because I was. Nearly a whole page is copy and pasted word for word from about 10 pages prior. And all the editorial errors aren''t the worst of it. This author can''t think of a more descriptive word than "crisp". It''s littered throughout the book. As for the story? Could be a story about two boats for all the science they didn''t have. Characters are cliche and there is zero mystery as for where the plot is going. How anyone gave this a decent review I''ll never know.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2247, 1707, 796, 5, 'This story represents one more  iteration of an historical fractal whose origin is rooted in the rise and evolution of civilizations: The confrontation of two mindsets, both rooted in obedience while one, however is totally dedicated to the good of its clan, only its clan, perish all others.Kudos to the author.Well done.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2248, 1708, 796, 4, 'Long to get into at the start and the writing style is not an intuitive match for me but despite that this story held me in until the very end.  60% of the way through it realy picks up as the two main protagonists start facing off directly. The  putting the book down is not an option.  Well do e and thoroughly enjoyed tjis one.  Now...  what else has this guy written.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2249, 1709, 796, 3, 'It was ok. It could have been so much better. After chapter after chapter of endless comparisons ... it all means nothing. The story took an easy predictable path that could have morphed into something far grander and complex ... but no. Enough for me. I won''t be continuing the series.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2250, 1710, 796, 4, 'This was a good novel ro read. The equally balanced  foes fight to the finish. I really liked all the characters and found them honourable.  Except for the real bad guys. I look forward to what happens next');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2251, 1711, 796, 5, 'Great military series and no spelling and grammar errors.  Thank you Jay Allen!A great series, the plot and story was excellent.  The series just gets better and better.  The battles were excellent and well written and not all of the characters safe to the end.  Could not put it down.  Too bad, I have to wait for the next book in the series.');
INSERT INTO public."Reviews" (review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, review) VALUES (2252, 1712, 796, 3, 'Very easy to read. It ha a simple plot line but it was difficult to understand the back story behind three empires. The use of Roman names crossed with US civil war type conflicts was never explained.');
